Hong Kong Approves Cathay, All Nippon, Singapore Fuel Surcharges

-- B y   J o s h u a   F e l l m a n
-- 
2011-02-18T14:04:47Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-18/hong-kong-approves-cathay-all-nippon-singapore-fuel-surcharges.html
Hong Kong’s Civil Aviation
Department approved increases in fuel surcharges by  Cathay
Pacific Airways Ltd ., All Nippon Airways Co. and Singapore
Airlines Ltd., according to a government statement today.     The surcharges by Cathay and Singapore will rise to HK$165
($21) per coupon from HK$143 for short-haul flights, and to
HK$747 from HK$677 for long haul flights, according to the
statement on the government’s website. All Nippon’s surcharge
will rise to HK$165 from HK$143.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joshua Fellman at 
 jfellman@bloomberg.net  